f claim 1 or 2, wherein at least one of said radially expandable units is configured to be in apposition with the interior vessel wall in the ascending aorta downstream said aortic valve and upstream all side branch vessels of said aortic arch. 4. The device of claim 1 -3, wherein said cover sheath has an increasing flexibility towards said distal end. 5. The device of claim 1 -4, wherein said cover sheath is elastic and has a lesser inner lumen diameter than an outer diameter of said delivery catheter, wherein said sheath is arranged 

 outside said delivery catheter by stretching over said delivery catheter's outside an along said delivery catheter outside. 6. The device of claim 1 -5, wherein said cover sheath has a length shorter than a length of said delivery catheter. 5 7. The device of claim 1 -5, combined with an introducer device configured to provide vascular, such as femoral access to said patients vascular system, said introducer having a shorter length than said delivery catheter, and a lower flexibility than said delivery catheter and said cover sheath. 8. The device of claims 1 -7, wherein said cover sheath includes with balloons/stabilizers 0 has distal end with orifice that ends proximally of delivery catheters distal end, sheath arranged coaxially outside of delivery catheter (preferably with low profile/diameter increase of delivery catheter). 9. The device of claims 1 -8, said cover sheath having a distal end with an attachment unit to the delivery catheter at the distal end of said cover sheath. 5 10. The device of claim 9, wherein said attachment unit is an adhesive unit, a force fit unit, such as said distal end contracting onto said delivery catheter, or a mechanical fixation unit, such as an outside ring, clamp, lock ring, hook, barb, or interference fit. 11. The device of any of claims 1 -10 including a slotted crown unit having a plurality of slots for passage of a portion of an interior inflation balloon and configured to produce lobes of said balloon o through said slots and radially outside said slots. 12. The device of any of claims 1 -11 said sheath having a lubricious inside, such as of PTFE, Teflon or Teflon coating. 13. The device of any of claims 1 -12, said sheath having a reinforcement braiding to avoid kinking. 5 14. The device of any of claims 1 -13 being a catheter device for transvascular delivery of a medical device to a target region, such as a heart valve region, of a patient, comprising an elongate sheath with a lumen, a proximal end, a distal end, and 