m 20 comprising: radially expanding expandable units of said catheter or an elongate member positioned 5 beyond a distal end of said sheath, to temporarily position in relation to said valve said elongate sheath; and optionally delivering a medical device through the lumen of said locked elongate sheath to said heart valve. 22. Method according to any of claims 20-21 comprising: inserting an elongate member with a distal end portion comprising a plurality of said radially 0 expandable units, into said lumen of said elongate sheath; advancing said elongate member through said elongate sheath to said distal end of said elongate sheath; 

